I found a concrete gap to close: source-ID frame features are only canonicalized when they include a 16-hex digest, so truncated/digestless `us-code` coordinates can degrade into noisy terms. I’m going to add a strict digestless fallback parser (`title` must look like a USC title), then add focused tests in selector and optimizer coverage.
apply patch
